[h1]Function Return[/h1]

Use the [b]return [/b]statement to return a value.

For example, let's calculate the product of two numbers, and return the result.[code format="js" codeId="680"]function myFunction(a, b) {
   [b]return [/b]a * b;
}

var x = myFunction(5, 6); 
// Return value will end up in x
// x equals 30[/code]
[note]If you do not return anything from a function, it will return [b]undefined[/b].[/note]

